comments: Drummond (DET) makes marginal contact with Sexton (CLE) at the end of his drive.
Thompson (CLE) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Mykhailiuk's (DET) path.
Drummond (DET) makes contact with Sexton's (CLE) arm after the release that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Mykhailiuk (DET) makes contact with Thompson's (CLE) body after the release that does not affect his play at the basket.
Garland (CLE) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Rose (DET).
Maker (DET) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Garland (CLE) and the contact is
Love (CLE) makes contact with the ball and marginal contact with Drummond's (DET) arm, but does not restrict Drummond's ability to secure the rebound.
Drummond (DET) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Sexton's (CLE) path and then legally rolls to the basket.
Maker (DET) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Osman (CLE).
Thompson (CLE) makes clean contact with the ball prior to making incidental arm contact with Maker (DET) during the rebound.
Thompson (CLE) makes incidental contact with Rose (DET) as the move in the same direction to retrieve the loose ball.
Thompson (CLE) initiates contact with Rose (DET) that affects his ability to defend.
Rose (DET) extends a forearm to Sexton's (CLE) side during his driving shot attempt.
Drummond (DET) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Dellavedova's (CLE) path.
Thompson (CLE) legally firms up in Brown's (DET) path and does not deliver any contact during the pick.
Drummond (DET) cleanly blocks Garland's (CLE) jump shot.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor was overturned. Sexton (CLE) legally remains inbound as he hovers his heel over the sideline, but does not make contact with the floor.
Rose (DET) makes marginal contact with Sexton (CLE) during his drive.
Rose (CLE) moves alongside Sexton's (CLE) body and maintains a legally collapsed forearm as he contests the driving shot attempt.
Drummond (DET) legally contests Sexton's (CLE) driving shot attempt and makes incidental body contact after his release.
Drummond (DET) makes contact with Sexton's (CLE) body after the release that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Sexton's (CLE) shot attempt fails to make contact with the rim resulting in a 24 second violation. The violation occurs prior to any contact to Thompson (CLE).
Osman (CLE) commits a take foul on Drummond (DET).
Thompson (CLE) grabs Maker's (DET) jersey during the rebound.
